					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Or a way that doesn't require one to be <a href="http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DrivenToSuicide" class="postlink">suicidal</a>: write a preprocessor in Perl or Python that outputs .byt statements, and have ca65 assemble <em>that</em>. This is like the macro way, but with the advantage of having more sophisticated syntax thanks to the regular expression facilities in such languages. It's also like the write-your-own-assembler way, but with the advantage that ca65 and ld65 handle all the label processing for you.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

