					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It bothers me because I use many different assemblers where a lot of things are different, and this is one extra thing. It is very uncomfortable to remember and relearn set of rules for every assembler.
<br />
<br />Examples are # or $ for hex, @ or . or _ for local labels, : after labels in some assemblers, etc.
<br />
<br />In many other assemblers block separator is : (and labels without : ). In 99% of assemblers ; is for comments.
<br />
<br />I can change it in the source, of course, but what will do people who would like to use my code? Change source too, or replace ; with //? It is kinda unconvenient.</div>

